    {"id":"post_1","type":"sharp_opinion","source_theme":"three_tens","text":"When an owner hesitates, it's rarely because the fee is 2 points too high. One of the certainty pillars is still wobbling.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"sharpest_observation","best_timing":"early_week","publish_after_linkedin":false,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"way_of_the_wolf","source_file":"linkedin/post_1.txt","theme":"three_tens","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_2","type":"recognition","source_theme":"commission_smokescreen","text":"Fee objections are often certainty problems with better manners.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"recognition_line","best_timing":"mid_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"way_of_the_wolf","source_file":"linkedin/post_2.txt","theme":"commission_smokescreen","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_2.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_3","type":"recognition","source_theme":"alchemist_trap","text":"Trying to close every owner with a pulse is how operators accidentally build a portfolio they don't enjoy running.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"recognition_line","best_timing":"mid_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"way_of_the_wolf","source_file":"linkedin/post_3.txt","theme":"alchemist_trap","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_3.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_4","type":"diagnostic","source_theme":"certainty_audit","text":"Useful post-appointment question: was the owner unconvinced about the system, the operator, or the brand? Discounting is the wrong answer to all three.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"tactical_question","best_timing":"after_post_1","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"way_of_the_wolf","source_file":"newsletter/newsletter.txt","theme":"certainty_audit","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_5","type":"story_detail","source_theme":"qualification_matrix","text":"A short qualification matrix before the pitch saves real time: hands-off or hands-on, worst prior experience, peak-season owner use. You'll know quickly whether the math and the relationship both work.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"story_detail","best_timing":"mid_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"way_of_the_wolf","source_file":"linkedin/post_3.txt","theme":"qualification_matrix","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_3.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_6","type":"engagement","source_theme":"certainty_gap_pattern","text":"Which certainty pillar breaks deals most often in your market right now: confidence in the system, confidence in the operator, or confidence in the brand behind the operator?","engagement_prompt":true,"post_role":"conversation_opener","best_timing":"late_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"way_of_the_wolf","source_file":"newsletter/newsletter.txt","theme":"certainty_gap_pattern","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_7","type":"author_engagement","source_theme":"author_application","text":"Jordan Belfort's certainty framing fits VRM well. Owners aren't buying a pitch. They're trying to get to enough certainty to hand over a very expensive, very personal asset.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"author_engagement","best_timing":"after_series_launch","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"way_of_the_wolf","source_file":"newsletter/newsletter.txt","theme":"author_application","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}}
